  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your feedback on your recent visit to the Emergency Department (ED) of Queen Elizabeth Hospital. We take all the feedbacks seriously and I apologise that you felt that your experience was short of your expectation.
We currently have visiting restrictions within the Trust however we do have exclusion criteria for vulnerable patients and those issued with a carer passport which allows them to be accompanied by their relations. Public Health England has advised that specific group of people are exempted from wearing masks due to specific reasons which might not always be visible hence you are likely to meet such group of people in the hospital when you visit. I apologise that the nurse did not take time to reassure you and clarify your queries which made you uncomfortable. Please be assured that all your concerns you have raised are acknowledged and will be highlighted to the ED team. Once again thank you for taking the time to let us know of your experience as we appraise and learn from all feedback and I wish you the best of health going forward.
All of our staff in the ED are trained to report and action areas of concern regarding cleanliness and infection control issue within a reasonable time frame. I apologise that this has not been the case on this occasion.

Your concerns around the nurse at the door and the cleanliness of the area have been reviewed and the relevant teams have been informed.  

Once again thank you for taking the time to let us know of your experience as we appraise and learn from all feedback and I wish you the best of health going forward. If you would like your concerns investigated further and receive a formal response, please contact the Patient Advice &amp;amp; Liaison Service (PALS) team at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital on 020 8836 4592

Glenda Moncar
ED Matron
Lewisham &amp;amp; Greenwich NHS Trust&lt;/CommentText&gt;
